<TEXT>
rebels killed a wellknown political activist 
and his eightyearold son stopping the activist and his family 
with gunfire as they took a sunday drive just outside lima police 
said 
arturo pacheco a a longtime member of the aprista party of 
former president alan garcia was killed by a dynamite charge 
placed on his chest after the rebels stopped the family car the 
police said 
they said pacheco had been driving on the main highway east of 
the city with his four children his wife and a male employee early 
sunday afternoon probably bound for his hog farm when they were 
attacked by seven people armed with automatic weapons and pistols 
pacheco and his eightyearold son were wounded by the gunfire 
police said and the attackers made his wife children and the 
employee step out of the vehicle and placed the dynamite charge on 
his chest 
they said the eightyearold son who died had been struck by 
three bullets 
authorities said the style and cruelty of the attack indicate it 
was carried out by maoistinspired shining path rebels 
more than 18000 people have died in political violence since 
the shining path began its war against the government 10 years ago 
