four brothers ranging in age from 1 to 7 
were killed saturday when a freight train going nearly 70 mph 
smashed into their stalled car as their frantic mother tried to 
flag the engineer and stop the locomotive 
the mother leoninia lendes 32 of delano got out of the way 
right at the last moment said police sgt don callahan 
trapped inside the wreckage were her children aged 1 4 6 and 
7 
the engineer told police he saw a woman waving and began to 
brake one block before impact the southern pacific train 
traveling nearly 70 mph and pulling about 100 cars had no chance to 
stop in time callahan said 
the train carried the auto wreckage for eight blocks before 
stopping the railroad crossing arm had dropped behind the 1990 
nissan sentra trapping it on the tracks 
we dont know why her car stalled she could possibly have 
panicked callahan said adding that the childrens mother was 
treated for emotional distress he said 
delano is a small farming community about 30 miles north of 
bakersfield trains travel through the center of town about once an 
hour callahan said 
