<TEXT>
a television station went off the air saturday 
night when police evacuated studios to conduct their third search 
of the day for a possible pizza restaurant robber 
after 25 minutes of dead air chicago station wlstv resumed 
broadcasting at a juryrigged studio in the sears tower it issued 
a special newscast to let viewers know what had happened 
the station then went off the air again 15 minutes later as 
police using scent dogs searched the 13story studio building 
a man thought to be armed with a pistol was seen entering the 
building saturday morning not long after a nearby pizza restaurant 
was robbed police said 
two daytime searches failed to locate the man but repeated 
sightings by station employees prompted the studio evacuation and 
third search at about 830 pm lt frank kehoe said 
theres no guarantee that this is the guy involved in the 
robbery kehoe added it could be just a trespasser 
wls general manager joe ahearn later said he would not allow 
employees to return until police were sure it was safe 
the station came back on the air at about 140 am sunday 
reporting in a 10minute news update that the search failed to find 
the man after the update the station went off the air again 
weve gone through every cubbyhole as well as the roof and 
around the satellite dishes said ahearn who accompanied police 
through the building i am absolutely confident that hes not in 
the building 
the television station is owned and operated by abc wls 
broadcasts are seen in eight counties in northern illinois two in 
northwestern indiana and two in southern wisconsin 
