irans foreign minister said sunday that 
foreigners fleeing iraq and kuwait can do so through iran 
according to tehran radio 
the report came after jordan and turkey complained that they are 
overburned by thousands of refugees and said they may have to close 
their borders 
syria iraqs main arab rival announced on saturday that it 
will allow foreigners to cross the syrian border with iraq 
most of the people who have fled iraq and kuwait since baghdad 
invaded its oilrich neighbor on aug 2 have entered jordan 
forcing it to feed and shelter them until they can afford to 
continue on to their home countries 
iran has condemned the invasion of kuwait and said it will 
enforce an international trade embargo against iraq 
but iran also recently settled disputes over territory and 
prisoners of war left unsettled by its long war with iraq and that 
allowed iraq to transfer thousands of troops from the iranian 
border and move them to occupied kuwait 
the tehran radio broadcast monitored in nicosia quoted foreign 
minister ali akbar velayati as saying that for humanitarian reasons 
iran agrees to foreign evacuees from iraq and kuwait transiting 
in its territory 
iran shares a 730milelong border with iraq 
