saturday last spoke with her husband around 5 am friday noon in 
kuwait she said that was saddams deadline for the american 
embassy to close 
i didnt sleep all night the night before mrs howell said 
howell reassured her that the embassy was safe she said he was 
eating lunch mrs howell said he was very calm 
mrs howell returned to the united states from kuwait on july 27 
to attend her fathers 84th birthday celebration she was aware of 
mounting tensions between iraq and kuwait she said but no one 
expected an invasion 
when i left there were 30000 iraqi troops sitting at the 
border but we thought that was saddam husseins way of extorting 
money from kuwait she said 
howell 51 was scheduled to step down as ambassador this month 
and join his wife as he resumed duties in washington he has served 
as ambassador to kuwait for three years and was in diplomatic 
positions in algiers lebanon and egypt 
this is our third war mrs howell said howell worked for 
the us foreign service in cairo during the sixday war in 1967 
and in beirut when lebanons civil war broke out in 1975 
howell graduated from the university of virginia in 1961 and 
received his doctorate in government and foreign affairs from the 
school in 1965 mrs howell is a graduate of the universitys 
nursing school 
university of virginia professor rk ramazani describes his 
former student as imaginative systematic hardworking and 
thorough 
