doing five stoves a month until now he said 
this growing interest comes as a sharp contrast to the 
industrys recent performance 
more than a decade ago the industry was growing so quickly that 
officials had no solid sales numbers they estimated annual stove 
sales exceeded 1 million around the start of the 1980s as large 
and small manufacturers proliferated around the country 
anybody that had a welding shop was putting together a wood 
