but for several reasons the industry shrank quickly annual 
sales are now estimated around 225000 
a big factor was the falling price of oil which meant people no 
longer were looking for another energy source instead wood stoves 
increasingly were bought for aesthetic reasons which meant they 
were competing with a new sofa or vcr said jason densmore of 
lebanon nh president of wood heating alliance a national trade 
association 
wood stoves also had a publicity problem mountain towns in 
colorado where air currents create special pollution problems 
restricted numbers of wood stoves in 1988 the us environmental 
protection agency set new rules for wood stoves forcing sharp 
reductions in smoke emissions 
meanwhile fatal house fires were reported across the country in 
which wood stoves were involved 
industry officials say however these accidents usually were 
due to improper installation of the stoves or poor maintenance of 
chimneys 
but these events have prompted the industry to change for the 
